14. g3 (14. Qxb4 {is well met by} Nxd5 $1 15. Qxb7+ Nxb7 16. Bxd8 Nxd8 $19)
14... Bxd5 15. Bh3+ Kc7 16. Qxb4 {0-1 Hagarova, Z (2321)-Womacka, M (2486)
Pardubice KB op 2000 (7) Black played in a safe way in the game, but even the
materialistic} Bxh1 17. Rxh1 Qb8 $19 {is good enough.}) (7. Bc4 b5 8. Bb3 Be7 {
transposes to 6.Bc4 e6 7.Bb3 b5 8.Bg5.}) (7. f3 {was tried by Carlsen in three
games and gained some popularity. The point is that White aims an English
Attack set-up against a Scheveningen structure - with pawns on e6 and d6
instead of e5 and d6, as in the classic English Attack move order. The obvious
drawback is that White is taking the risk of wasting at least one tempo with
