the normal Scheveningen set-up is playable for Black, so going for it with a
tempo-up is not a problem. However, this could be a clever strategy to
surprise a player who is not familiar with this structure, so we should study
some ideas.} Be7 8. Qd2 b5 $1 {This quick advance is recommended by Giri,
keeping the knight flexible on b8.} 9. O-O-O {As the e4-pawn is already safe,
White can simply castle.} (9. a3 {avoids ideas with b5-b4, but Black continues
with} Bb7 10. O-O-O Nc6 $5 {an interesting idea based on a pawn sacrifice.} 11.
Be3 {Now we've transposed to a position of the Classical Sicilian with a tempo
