{After analyzing more direct plans, in this chapter we will see calmer
variations, which I decided to call quiet lines. Here, instead of going for
concrete and more tense positions, White chooses a more positional approach,
with slower plans, maneuvers, and subtle ideas, aiming for a tiny advantage
and an easier game. Studying the lines seen in this chapter will improve your
positional understanding of Najdorf positions and will prevent you from
falling for small positional threats, typical of less popular variations.} 1.
