idea is to transpose to a sort of English Attack where Black has played e6
instead of e5. The drawback is that the bishop should be on e3 instead of g5
in such positions, and this tempo can prove to be very useful for Black.} Be7
8. Qd2 b5 $1 {We can make this advance right now. An interesting point is to
keep the Nb8 flexible for a while.} 9. O-O-O (9. a3 {avoids b4, but Black can
continue with} Bb7 10. O-O-O Nc6 $5 {an interesting idea based on a pawn
