Ne6+ Ke8 17. Ng7+ Kf8 18. Ne6+ $11) 7... h6 8. Bh4 ({In case of} 8. Bxf6 Qxf6
9. Qd2 g5 $1 {is the most direct to equalize. After} 10. f5 Bg7 11. O-O-O Qxd4
12. Qxd4 Bxd4 13. Rxd4 Ke7 $11 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gb8c6,Gc6e5] ;Paravyan,D (2620)
-Robson, R (2682) Chess.com Rapid Wk23 Swiss 2022 (7) 1-0 Black has a solid
position.}) 8... Qb6 9. a3 {White's best chance of fighting for an advantage.}
(9. Qd2 {is the classical approach, sacrificing the pawn for active play and a
